<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<%- include('../layout', { seo, baseUrl }) %>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Manrope:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
*{box-sizing:border-box}body{margin:0;font-family:'Manrope',sans-serif;background:#0a0d12;color:#f5f7fb;line-height:1.7}a{text-decoration:none;color:inherit}.wrap{width:min(980px,calc(100% - 32px));margin:0 auto}.top{padding:24px 0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08)}.top-in{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:16px}.brand{font-size:22px;font-weight:800}.brand span{color:#d7b35d}.links{display:flex;gap:16px;flex-wrap:wrap;color:#9ea8bb}.hero{padding:64px 0 24px}.hero h1{font-size:clamp(36px,7vw,62px);line-height:1.04;margin:0 0 12px}.hero p{max-width:760px;color:#b2bccf}.section{padding:18px 0 42px}.card{background:#121722;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);border-radius:24px;padding:28px;margin-top:18px}.card h2{margin:0 0 12px;font-size:28px}.card h3{margin:22px 0 8px;font-size:19px}.card p,.card li{color:#d9e1ef}.card ol,.card ul{padding-left:20px}.muted{color:#9ea8bb}.footer{padding:30px 0 40px;border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08)}.footer-links{display:flex;gap:14px;flex-wrap:wrap;color:#9ea8bb}@media (max-width:720px){.top-in{align-items:flex-start;flex-direction:column}}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<header class="top">
  <div class="wrap top-in">
    <a href="/" class="brand">VibeNote<span>.studio</span></a>
    <nav class="links" aria-label="Site links">
      <a href="/docs">Docs</a>
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>
      <a href="/terms">Terms</a>
      <a href="/cookies">Cookies</a>
    </nav>
  </div>
</header>
<main>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="muted">Documentation</p>
      <h1>How agencies use VibeNote to deliver small client websites faster.</h1>
      <p>VibeNote is an agency delivery system for landing pages, brochure websites, small business websites, and portfolio websites. It helps teams move from brief to generated website to live deployment without spending senior dev time on low-ticket builds.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="card">
        <h2>What VibeNote is</h2>
        <p>VibeNote is a Node.js SaaS platform for agencies that need to create, edit, and deploy static client websites quickly. It is designed for websites built with HTML, CSS, and minimal JavaScript rather than database-driven applications.</p>
        <h3>How agencies use the platform</h3>
        <p>Agencies create an account, collect a structured client brief, let the AI generate a polished static website, make edits through the editor, and then deploy using Cloudflare Pages, FTP hosting, or HTML export.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Agency workflow</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Create an agency account and set up your delivery workflow.</li>
          <li>Fill the client brief with business details, services, brand direction, assets, and contact information.</li>
          <li>The AI generates a responsive client website using static HTML, CSS, and minimal JavaScript.</li>
          <li>Edit content and design details inside the VibeNote editor.</li>
          <li>Deploy to Cloudflare Pages, client FTP hosting, or export the static files.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Deployment options</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Cloudflare Pages for fast static hosting and live URLs.</li>
          <li>FTP deployment for client hosting environments.</li>
          <li>Static HTML export when your team wants to hand over files directly.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>
<footer class="footer">
  <div class="wrap top-in">
    <div class="muted">VibeNote helps agencies generate, edit, and deploy client websites instantly.</div>
    <div class="footer-links">
      <a href="/docs">Docs</a>
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
      <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>
      <a href="/cookies">Cookie Policy</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</footer>
</body>
</html>
